pageContext.claim: “People that graduate without a high school diploma -- it's a big group -- lowest in the history of our country.”
pageContext.analysis: This dataset has only be recorded since 1992, so Trump has no basis to claim the "history of our country." The unemployment rate for high school dropouts reached a low of 5.0 percent in July 2018, but by the time Trump made this statement it had risen to 5.9 percent, a figure last reached in 2000.
